()CertificationDefinition kya karta hai?
👉 CertificationDefinition = Certification ka template / blueprint
Matlab:-
“Certification ka design kaise hoga” ye define karta hai

🔥 Simple Example:-
Tu bolta hai:-
Kaunse users ka review hoga
Kaun reviewer hoga
Kaunsa access include hoga
Rules kya honge
👉 Ye sab define hota hai → CertificationDefinition.

🔹 Ye kya karta hai?
👉 Ye decide karta hai:-
Certification ka type (Manager, Application, Role)
Scope (kaunse users / systems)
Review rules
Policy checks
Reminder / escalation rules

🔹 Real Flow samajh le:-
CertificationDefinition (template)
        ↓
CertificationSchedule (kab run hoga)
        ↓
Certification (actual run)
        ↓
CertificationItem (individual access)

🔹 Kya DB me store hota hai?
👉 ✅ Haan bhai, ye DB me store hota hai
🔸 Table:-
spt_certification_definition

🔹 CertificationDefinition ke andar kya hota hai?
🔸 1️⃣ Basic Info:-
id
name
description

🔸 2️⃣ Certification Type:-
Manager Certification
Application Certification
Role Certification

🔸 3️⃣ Scope (bahut important 🔥):-
identities (users)
applications
roles
groups

🔸 4️⃣ Reviewer Setup:-
reviewer (manager / owner)
fallback reviewer
escalation rules

🔸 5️⃣ Rules / Logic:-
inclusion rule
exclusion rule
policy violation rule

🔸 6️⃣ Settings:-
autoSignOff
reminders
due date
reassign allowed

🔸 7️⃣ Advanced:-
phase configuration
decision options
comments required ya nahi.

🔹 Methods ka idea:-
🔸 Basic Methods:-
getId()
setId()
getName()
setName()
🔸 Type Methods:-
getType()
setType()
🔸 Scope Methods:-
getScope()
setScope()
🔸 Reviewer Methods:-
getReviewer()
setReviewer()
🔸 Settings Methods:-
isAutoSignOff()
setAutoSignOff()
🔸 Utility Methods:-
toString()
equals()
hashCode()
🔸 Rule Methods:-
getInclusionRule()
setInclusionRule()
setExclusionRule()
getExclusionRule()

🔹 🔸 getInclusionRule():-
👉 Ye method current inclusion rule ka naam/object return karta hai
🔸 Example:-
System.out.println(definition.getInclusionRule());
✅ Output:-
OnlyActiveUsers
👉 Matlab:-
Certification me sirf active users include honge

🔹 🔸 setInclusionRule():-
👉 Ye method kaunsa inclusion rule use hoga wo set karta hai
🔸 Example:-
definition.setInclusionRule("OnlyActiveUsers");
👉 Ab system:-
Sirf active users ko include karega

🔹 🔸 getExclusionRule():-
👉 Ye method current exclusion rule return karta hai
🔸 Example:-
System.out.println(definition.getExclusionRule());
✅ Output:-
ExcludeAdmins
👉 Matlab:-
Admin users remove kiye jayenge

🔹 🔸 setExclusionRule():-
👉 Ye method kaunsa exclusion rule apply hoga wo set karta hai
🔸 Example:-
definition.setExclusionRule("ExcludeAdmins");
👉 Ab system:-
Admin users ko certification se hata dega ❌
-----------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 Full Flow Example (Best Samajh 🔥)
definition.setInclusionRule("OnlyActiveUsers");
definition.setExclusionRule("ExcludeAdmins");

System.out.println(definition.getInclusionRule());
System.out.println(definition.getExclusionRule());

✅ Output:-
OnlyActiveUsers
ExcludeAdmins
------------------------------------------------------------------
()🔹 🔥 Inclusion Rule kya hai?
👉 Inclusion Rule = Kaun include hoga certification me
Matlab:-
“Kin users / accounts / access ko certification me lana hai”

🔸 Example:-
definition.setInclusionRule("OnlyActiveUsers");

👉 Rule logic:-
if(user.isActive()){
   return true; // include karo
}
✅ Result:-
Sirf active users certification me aayenge.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 🔥 Exclusion Rule kya hai?
👉 Exclusion Rule = Kisko hataana hai (filter out)
Matlab:-
“Jo include ho chuke hain unme se kisko remove karna hai”

🔸 Example:-
definition.setExclusionRule("ExcludeAdmins");

👉 Rule logic:-
if(user.role == "Admin"){
   return true; // exclude karo
}
✅ Result:-
Admin users ❌ remove ho jayenge
Baaki sab rahenge.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 🔸 isAutoSignOff():-
👉 Ye method batata hai:-
“Certification automatically complete hoga ya nahi?”

🔸 Example:-
System.out.println(definition.isAutoSignOff());

✅ Output:-
true

👉 Matlab:-
System automatically certification close kar dega
Reviewer ko manually sign-off nahi karna padega.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 🔸 setAutoSignOff():-
👉 Ye method decide karta hai:-
“Auto sign-off enable karna hai ya nahi”

🔸 Example:-
definition.setAutoSignOff(true);

👉 Matlab:-
Certification automatically complete ho jayega ✅
-----------------------------------------------------------------
